In this op-ed, Mary B. Neumayr, Chairman of the Council on Environmental Quality, highlights President Trump's commitment to conservation and environmental stewardship. She mentions that he has signed legislation to expand recreational access to public lands, support land and water conservation, and protect national parks. President Trump has also prioritized active forest management to reduce wildfire risk and has joined the One Trillion Trees Initiative to promote international conservation efforts. Additionally, he has directed the implementation of more efficient air quality standards, resulting in cleaner air and a significant decline in energy-related carbon dioxide emissions.